ration to be\nnearly 3.2 pc; even so, $>76\\%$ of GAMBLES long-lived binaries have large\nbinding energies and dissipation lifetimes longer than 1.5 Gyr. Finally, we\nfind the distribution of binary separations is clearly bimodal, corroborating\nthe finding from SloWPoKES and suggesting multiple pathways for the formation\nand dissipation of the widest binaries in the Galaxy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Nov 2016 17:02:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 27 Nov 2016 21:05:38 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 14 Apr 2017 14:57:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-31"}
